<TITLE> Nazmul Huda nailed in another corruption case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Munshiganj, June 1 (bdnews24.com)- A Tk 4.55 crore corruption case has been filed against former communications minister Barrister Nazmul Huda with Munshiganj Sadar Police Station, police said Friday. Sub-inspector Asaduzzaman said a former executive engineer of the Roads and Highways Department, Arifur Rahman, had filed the case. According to case details, Huda engaged in massive corruption in different projects in Munshiganj and intimidated Arifur Rahman when he was the executive engineer of Munshiganj RHD for 2002-2005. Rahman is now working as the superintending engineer at the RHD headquarters. Joint forces arrested Huda on Feb 4. On March 6, Ayub Ali of Dohar filed a case with Dohar Police Station against five people, including Huda and brother Kamrul Huda for extortion. A Dhaka court on March 11 rejected the bail petition of Huda in connection with the case filed against him for extorting Tk 2 lakh in 2004. In another development, Dhanmondi police on April 10 pressed charges against Huda for possessing illegal firearms and ammunition. The joint forces seized a revolver, 14 bullets, a huge amount of local and foreign currencies, four passports and a mobile phone set from Huda's Dhanmondi home on Feb 4the day he was arrested. A case was filed under the Arms Act on March 8. Sub-inspector AKM Monzurul Haq Akand filed another case on Feb 15 for illegally possessing a huge amount of foreign and local currencies under the Money Laundering Act. The former communications minister was widely accused of making huge money through corruption relating to CNG-run autorickshaws and allocation of land for filling stations during the tenure of the immediate past BNP-led four-party alliance government. Huda even allotted a costly piece of Bangladesh Railway land in the heart of the city for his wife's human rights organisation at lower-than-market prices. bdnews24.c
